1
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:34,918
=Vanished Name=

2
00:01:35,224 --> 00:01:37,656
= Episode 29 =
(Be Each Other's Light)

3
00:02:05,240 --> 00:02:06,440
You filmed the video?

4
00:02:08,600 --> 00:02:09,919
And you took the gun?

5
00:02:11,239 --> 00:02:12,639
You're that witness?

6
00:02:13,079 --> 00:02:14,000
Don't worry.

7
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:17,199
I will handle everything for you.

8
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:23,880
If it were a stranger,

9
00:02:24,639 --> 00:02:26,519
Ren Xiaoming and I
would still have a chance.

10
00:02:27,720 --> 00:02:29,079
But she took the gun.

11
00:02:30,799 --> 00:02:32,400
So we had zero chance.

12
00:02:33,528 --> 00:02:34,199
(Qidaohezi, 2010)

13
00:02:34,199 --> 00:02:36,079
(So I decided to record the truth)

14
00:02:36,320 --> 00:02:38,720
(with invisible ink in the diary.)

15
00:02:51,440 --> 00:02:54,720
(In 2010, when I was burying the ashes
of the deceased in the back hill,)

16
00:02:55,359 --> 00:02:56,600
(Zhou Na came to see me.)

17
00:02:57,239 --> 00:02:59,519
(She said she killed Wang Hao.)

18
00:03:04,199 --> 00:03:05,479
After Zhou Na died,

19
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:08,000
I returned to Qingzhou.

20
00:03:09,120 --> 00:03:10,679
In about three months,

21
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:14,880
I applied for an exchange program
and went abroad early.

22
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:18,232
(Qingzhou Airport, 2010)

23
00:03:36,088 --> 00:03:38,744
(International Departures)

24
00:03:39,479 --> 00:03:40,239
Why did you come?

25
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:46,519
Take the diary.
Go as far away as possible.

26
00:03:52,679 --> 00:03:53,600
Don't ever come back.

27
00:04:00,320 --> 00:04:02,239
Go ahead. I won't see you off.

28
00:04:07,960 --> 00:04:09,976
(International Departures)

29
00:04:48,559 --> 00:04:51,720
(We agreed
never to see each other again.)

30
00:05:36,152 --> 00:05:38,520
(Contacts: Ren Xiaoming)

31
00:05:44,888 --> 00:05:45,880
(Delete contact of Ren Xiaoming)

32
00:05:45,880 --> 00:05:46,488
(Deleting)

33
00:05:50,168 --> 00:05:53,240
(Contacts: Ge Wenjun)

34
00:05:53,368 --> 00:05:54,552
(Ge Wenjun, Connecting)

35
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:01,200
Stop looking for me.

36
00:06:01,760 --> 00:06:02,840
I'm going home now.

37
00:06:04,879 --> 00:06:06,359
I've sent Ren Xiaoming away.

38
00:06:07,559 --> 00:06:08,840
I won't see her again.

39
00:06:10,640 --> 00:06:11,280
Great.

40
00:06:13,879 --> 00:06:14,439
From now on,

41
00:06:16,119 --> 00:06:18,919
you and I will live happily together,

42
00:06:20,359 --> 00:06:21,400
forever and ever.

43
00:06:29,559 --> 00:06:30,640
You just said

44
00:06:31,239 --> 00:06:33,840
that Bai Shu
took it upon herself to save you.

45
00:06:34,319 --> 00:06:35,280
Didn't you do the same?

46
00:06:37,080 --> 00:06:38,679
Sorry, I don't understand.

47
00:06:38,919 --> 00:06:40,319
Yes, you do.

48
00:06:41,919 --> 00:06:43,439
You didn't know about the video.

49
00:06:43,879 --> 00:06:47,280
You had no evidence
to prove you were the murderer.

50
00:06:48,160 --> 00:06:50,600
So you used reverse psychology.

51
00:06:50,879 --> 00:06:52,439
You hid evidence, transferred assets,

52
00:06:52,879 --> 00:06:54,960
and fabricated mental illness
as if trying

53
00:06:55,359 --> 00:06:56,600
to avoid conviction.

54
00:06:56,879 --> 00:06:58,160
But in fact, you were trying

55
00:06:58,439 --> 00:07:00,600
to make us believe
that you were the murderer

56
00:07:01,160 --> 00:07:02,679
through your behavior.

57
00:07:03,840 --> 00:07:05,840
Too bad you didn't know

58
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:08,119
Bai Shu had hidden records in her diary,

59
00:07:08,799 --> 00:07:12,280
which described in detail
how she killed Zhou Na with the pen.

60
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:19,999
There were earlier flights to Qingzhou.

61
00:07:20,640 --> 00:07:22,559
But you booked Xiaoyu on the next one.

62
00:07:23,840 --> 00:07:26,520
Because this flight number plus the time

63
00:07:27,040 --> 00:07:28,239
matched your password.

64
00:07:29,400 --> 00:07:30,239
"Goodbye."

65
00:07:44,879 --> 00:07:45,464
Bai Shu.

66
00:07:47,799 --> 00:07:49,119
Didn't we agree on it?

67
00:07:53,720 --> 00:07:56,319
The moment you led me to find the diary,

68
00:07:57,239 --> 00:07:59,879
you decided to take the blame
for Ren Xiaoming.

69
00:08:01,960 --> 00:08:05,280
You planned to turn yourself in
the moment Xiaoyu landed.

70
00:08:05,559 --> 00:08:09,200
You calculated when you'd be arrested.

71
00:08:17,840 --> 00:08:20,679
You two were saying goodbye
to each other.

72
00:08:23,119 --> 00:08:24,640
If it weren't for Bai Shu,

73
00:08:26,280 --> 00:08:28,160
my world would've been coin-sized.

74
00:08:28,879 --> 00:08:31,879
She always said
I was smarter and better than her

75
00:08:33,160 --> 00:08:35,679
and that she became better
by chasing my shadow.

76
00:08:36,280 --> 00:08:37,360
At first,

77
00:08:39,919 --> 00:08:40,559
I admired her.

78
00:08:42,319 --> 00:08:43,719
Then I envied her.

79
00:08:45,439 --> 00:08:46,439
Then,

80
00:08:48,559 --> 00:08:50,079
I feared I wasn't good enough.

81
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:53,480
I feared I'd disappoint her.

82
00:08:54,640 --> 00:08:58,040
But actually, she surpassed me long ago.

83
00:09:00,199 --> 00:09:02,799
I've admired and envied her.

84
00:09:04,679 --> 00:09:07,799
But I genuinely hope
that she could go further.

85
00:09:09,199 --> 00:09:12,520
So I just kept going

86
00:09:14,120 --> 00:09:15,199
farther away.

87
00:09:21,240 --> 00:09:22,679
My world grew

88
00:09:23,880 --> 00:09:25,040
bigger and bigger.

89
00:09:27,199 --> 00:09:27,959
Bai Shu.

90
00:09:30,880 --> 00:09:32,120
It's because of Bai Shu.

91
00:09:36,040 --> 00:09:37,799
I turned that coin into a moon.

92
00:09:38,319 --> 00:09:40,280
Because when she became the moon,

93
00:09:41,280 --> 00:09:43,120
no matter what nightmare I'm in,

94
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:47,439
that light will never go out.

95
00:10:22,880 --> 00:10:23,544
Get up.

96
00:10:39,839 --> 00:10:40,760
Don't touch my fridge.

97
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:41,880
Buy your own water.

98
00:10:42,719 --> 00:10:43,959
Nice sparkling water.

99
00:10:44,719 --> 00:10:45,439
Want some?

100
00:10:47,280 --> 00:10:49,319
So stingy with sparkling water.

101
00:10:51,360 --> 00:10:53,000
Ren Xiaoming treated you like dirt.

102
00:10:53,199 --> 00:10:54,232
Haven't you had enough?

103
00:10:54,520 --> 00:10:57,799
See, she got herself arrested now.

104
00:10:58,040 --> 00:11:00,319
You're free without lifting a finger.

105
00:11:01,079 --> 00:11:03,040
This is your happiest moment.

106
00:11:03,199 --> 00:11:04,599
Chen Junhang, you are so heartless?

107
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:06,000
Stop this nonsense.

108
00:11:06,839 --> 00:11:08,599
I'm just kidding. Chill.

109
00:11:09,640 --> 00:11:10,240
Seriously.

110
00:11:18,400 --> 00:11:20,839
I know, you are married after all.

111
00:11:21,959 --> 00:11:24,079
I'll find you
a top criminal defense lawyer, okay?

112
00:11:24,799 --> 00:11:27,000
Mr. Luo. He'll do, right?

113
00:11:28,280 --> 00:11:29,360
So grumpy.

114
00:11:29,599 --> 00:11:30,439
Seriously.

115
00:11:31,919 --> 00:11:32,919
Tell me one thing.

116
00:11:34,079 --> 00:11:35,839
The book is back on the shelves.

117
00:11:36,199 --> 00:11:38,199
Why aren't you
sharing the profits with me?

118
00:11:39,880 --> 00:11:41,240
So that's why you're upset?

119
00:11:41,760 --> 00:11:42,480
Isn't it obvious?

120
00:11:43,319 --> 00:11:44,079
Here's the thing.

121
00:11:45,120 --> 00:11:47,199
This book was plagiarized.

122
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:50,000
Putting it back on sale carries risks.

123
00:11:50,919 --> 00:11:53,799
Your share of the profits
has been given to the publisher

124
00:11:54,199 --> 00:11:55,000
for risk control.

125
00:11:55,360 --> 00:11:56,439
Are you kidding me?

126
00:11:57,079 --> 00:11:58,919
Shouldn't we share the risk?

127
00:11:59,319 --> 00:12:00,319
I'm the money maker.

128
00:12:00,599 --> 00:12:01,640
Why can't I get my share?

129
00:12:02,719 --> 00:12:04,439
Don't make a big deal out of this.

130
00:12:04,439 --> 00:12:05,679
What's the point of all this

131
00:12:05,719 --> 00:12:06,959
if I don't care about money?

132
00:12:07,240 --> 00:12:09,360
You're making money
because they promote you.

133
00:12:09,919 --> 00:12:11,079
You're in trouble.

134
00:12:11,559 --> 00:12:12,760
It's best to lie low.

135
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:14,280
If you keep nitpicking,

136
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:15,880
you may lose everything.

137
00:12:19,520 --> 00:12:20,319
What about

138
00:12:20,640 --> 00:12:22,360
my share of the money?

139
00:12:23,079 --> 00:12:25,679
Don't cause trouble now, okay?

140
00:12:43,679 --> 00:12:44,240
Hello?

141
00:12:45,799 --> 00:12:47,120
Yeah, it's me.

142
00:12:54,240 --> 00:12:54,959
What happened?

143
00:12:55,736 --> 00:12:56,600
Yes.

144
00:13:07,480 --> 00:13:08,360
Okay, I got it.

145
00:13:11,319 --> 00:13:12,040
Thank you.

146
00:13:18,280 --> 00:13:18,839
What happened?

147
00:13:21,959 --> 00:13:22,959
Xiaoming is pregnant.

148
00:13:27,400 --> 00:13:28,160
They said

149
00:13:29,079 --> 00:13:29,880
she's pregnant.

150
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:32,400
You hit the jackpot.

151
00:13:35,839 --> 00:13:37,959
This is a golden opportunity.

152
00:13:38,959 --> 00:13:40,719
We have to seize this chance.

153
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:41,559
Let me think.

154
00:13:43,280 --> 00:13:44,319
How many do you have?

155
00:13:44,520 --> 00:13:46,240
How many what?

156
00:13:46,319 --> 00:13:49,079
Marketing accounts. Use all of them.

157
00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:51,640
We need to act fast right now.

158
00:13:52,319 --> 00:13:53,319
Seize the opportunity.

159
00:13:53,679 --> 00:13:55,160
Contact the publisher

160
00:13:55,360 --> 00:13:56,480
and the platforms.

161
00:13:58,079 --> 00:13:59,040
First of all,

162
00:13:59,559 --> 00:14:00,760
reach out to everyone.

163
00:14:01,280 --> 00:14:02,599
We must grab this chance

164
00:14:03,040 --> 00:14:03,919
to turn the tide.

165
00:14:06,280 --> 00:14:07,640
Due to the reprint controversy,

166
00:14:08,160 --> 00:14:09,679
(Breathe)
your book was taken down.

167
00:14:10,160 --> 00:14:13,319
It was put back on the shelves yesterday

168
00:14:14,160 --> 00:14:16,520
(Breathe)
and topped the bestseller charts soon.

169
00:14:17,199 --> 00:14:17,839
Congratulations.

170
00:14:18,360 --> 00:14:18,919
Thank you.

171
00:14:20,520 --> 00:14:23,400
(Nice place for an interview.)
But do you think its success

172
00:14:23,839 --> 00:14:26,240
(Fortune and misfortune coexist.)
is related to the arrest of your wife

173
00:14:26,584 --> 00:14:27,599
(Stay calm amid the crisis.)
Ren Xiaoming?

174
00:14:27,896 --> 00:14:28,959
(Hi, guys.)
What do you think?

175
00:14:28,959 --> 00:14:29,816
(More gossip.)

176
00:14:29,816 --> 00:14:30,760
(I love juicy gossip.)

177
00:14:30,760 --> 00:14:33,559
(Hi, guys.)
Some troublemakers online

178
00:14:33,839 --> 00:14:36,079
(Let's see how it goes.)
say the fictional murder in my novel

179
00:14:36,632 --> 00:14:37,720
(Rumors don't start without a reason.)
is related

180
00:14:38,360 --> 00:14:40,319
(Tell the truth.)
to the case my wife is involved with.

181
00:14:40,319 --> 00:14:41,208
(Nice bookstore for interview.)

182
00:14:41,208 --> 00:14:42,360
(Take your time.)

183
00:14:42,360 --> 00:14:45,280
(Nice book. I like it.)
I put the book back on the shelves,

184
00:14:45,880 --> 00:14:49,240
(Have a bottom line.)
so more people

185
00:14:50,319 --> 00:14:52,799
(I've been following it.)
can read the original text.

186
00:14:53,520 --> 00:14:55,079
I believe the readers

187
00:14:55,919 --> 00:14:58,360
will form a rational judgment.

188
00:14:59,120 --> 00:15:02,319
But some are already accusing you
of profiting from tragedy.

189
00:15:04,079 --> 00:15:04,959
I've heard that too.

190
00:15:05,719 --> 00:15:07,280
People were saying

191
00:15:07,520 --> 00:15:11,199
that I leaked Xiaoming's videos online.

192
00:15:12,319 --> 00:15:13,839
Many people said that.

193
00:15:15,079 --> 00:15:16,799
But I don't want to dwell on

194
00:15:17,400 --> 00:15:18,400
such claims.

195
00:15:19,079 --> 00:15:20,480
My top priority

196
00:15:21,079 --> 00:15:22,199
is my wife's case.

197
00:15:23,760 --> 00:15:27,439
It's been the darkest time of my life.

198
00:15:30,400 --> 00:15:32,120
I didn't know

199
00:15:32,719 --> 00:15:35,480
why Xiaoming suddenly wanted a divorce.

200
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:38,040
Now I understand.

201
00:15:38,679 --> 00:15:39,400
Can you explain?

202
00:15:42,120 --> 00:15:45,079
Mr. Xu, could I take this opportunity

203
00:15:45,599 --> 00:15:46,640
to tell her something?

204
00:15:47,240 --> 00:15:47,760
Of course.

205
00:15:53,592 --> 00:15:54,776
(Learn to let go.)

206
00:15:54,776 --> 00:15:55,992
(Everyone has their problems,)

207
00:15:55,992 --> 00:15:57,080
(with different perspectives.)

208
00:15:57,080 --> 00:15:58,040
(Wish you the best.)

209
00:15:58,040 --> 00:15:58,679
(Keep watching.)
Xiaoming.

210
00:15:58,679 --> 00:15:59,704
(He looks worn out.)

211
00:15:59,704 --> 00:16:00,504
(What happened?)

212
00:16:00,504 --> 00:16:01,559
(Everything changed for him.)

213
00:16:01,559 --> 00:16:02,839
(Agreed.)
No matter what you've done,

214
00:16:04,799 --> 00:16:06,280
(It's a problem)
please don't push me away.

215
00:16:06,280 --> 00:16:07,320
(for many people.)

216
00:16:07,320 --> 00:16:08,216
(I just heard about it.)

217
00:16:08,216 --> 00:16:09,240
(Trust your feeling.)

218
00:16:09,240 --> 00:16:10,360
(So different.)
We are married.

219
00:16:10,360 --> 00:16:11,096
(Hang in there.)

220
00:16:11,096 --> 00:16:11,880
(Let's see.)

221
00:16:11,880 --> 00:16:13,079
(I support you.)
We love each other.

222
00:16:13,079 --> 00:16:13,912
(This place is buzzing.)

223
00:16:13,912 --> 00:16:14,760
(He looks helpless.)

224
00:16:14,760 --> 00:16:16,880
I promised to be with you
through thick and thin.

225
00:16:16,880 --> 00:16:17,880
(Let's wait and see.)

226
00:16:17,880 --> 00:16:18,872
(Wait for the truth.)

227
00:16:18,872 --> 00:16:19,512
(No rush.)

228
00:16:19,512 --> 00:16:20,240
(Having a child might help.)

229
00:16:20,240 --> 00:16:21,480
(Still not done?)
My wedding vow.

230
00:16:21,480 --> 00:16:22,392
(Don't break them up.)

231
00:16:22,392 --> 00:16:23,352
(Try harder.)

232
00:16:23,352 --> 00:16:24,319
(Gets me anxious.)

233
00:16:24,319 --> 00:16:25,919
(What's going on?)
Nothing but death

234
00:16:27,559 --> 00:16:29,520
(Everyone makes mistakes.)
can separate us.

235
00:16:29,520 --> 00:16:30,520
(Make it right.)

236
00:16:30,520 --> 00:16:31,704
(Face the problem.)

237
00:16:31,704 --> 00:16:32,792
(Things will get better.)

238
00:16:32,792 --> 00:16:33,752
(All marketing accounts?)

239
00:16:33,752 --> 00:16:34,552
(Remember the original intention.)

240
00:16:34,552 --> 00:16:35,360
(Reliable guy.)

241
00:16:35,360 --> 00:16:36,360
I will always love you.

242
00:16:36,360 --> 00:16:37,432
(Let's be objective.)

243
00:16:37,432 --> 00:16:38,328
(Analyze it calmly.)

244
00:16:38,328 --> 00:16:39,320
(Don't be emotional.)

245
00:16:39,320 --> 00:16:40,280
(Empathy is crucial.)

246
00:16:40,280 --> 00:16:41,144
(I tend to be subjective.)

247
00:16:41,144 --> 00:16:41,880
(Be objective.)

248
00:16:48,480 --> 00:16:50,072
- Thanks for the interview.
- Let's meet again.

249
00:16:59,199 --> 00:17:00,679
Captain Li, your coffee.

250
00:17:01,599 --> 00:17:02,120
Thank you.

251
00:17:03,439 --> 00:17:04,760
How did it go?

252
00:17:05,520 --> 00:17:06,200
All settled.

253
00:17:06,440 --> 00:17:08,359
We took Ren Xiaoming to the hospital.

254
00:17:08,359 --> 00:17:09,639
No major health issues.

255
00:17:09,879 --> 00:17:11,359
We notified the family as required.

256
00:17:12,639 --> 00:17:13,200
Good.

257
00:17:15,680 --> 00:17:16,240
Ma'am.

258
00:17:17,240 --> 00:17:17,839
Huang Yue.

259
00:17:17,839 --> 00:17:18,920
You scared me.

260
00:17:18,920 --> 00:17:20,680
- Sorry.
- What's the rush?

261
00:17:21,119 --> 00:17:22,399
The forensics gave me this.

262
00:17:22,648 --> 00:17:23,720
(Forensic Report)
What is this?

263
00:17:23,720 --> 00:17:24,280
(Statement)

264
00:17:24,680 --> 00:17:26,720
Wang Hao gave us some of Zhou Na's hair

265
00:17:26,720 --> 00:17:29,000
and medical information the other day.

266
00:17:29,480 --> 00:17:30,359
Here are the results.

267
00:17:30,392 --> 00:17:32,472
(V. Expert Evaluation)

268
00:17:32,760 --> 00:17:33,760
(Through DNA comparison,
it's not the same person)

269
00:17:33,760 --> 00:17:35,928
The corpse in the concrete base
is not Zhou Na's body.

270
00:17:42,040 --> 00:17:43,200
Who killed Zhou Na?

271
00:17:43,680 --> 00:17:44,480
I did.

272
00:17:45,040 --> 00:17:45,839
Be more specific.

273
00:17:49,159 --> 00:17:52,200
It is me who strangled her

274
00:17:52,799 --> 00:17:53,760
with her bag's chain.

275
00:17:54,359 --> 00:17:55,119
Where's her body?

276
00:17:59,639 --> 00:18:00,760
At Qidian Middle School.

277
00:18:01,639 --> 00:18:03,119
In the statue base.

278
00:18:04,319 --> 00:18:05,159
I'll ask you again.

279
00:18:05,920 --> 00:18:07,720
Who killed her?

280
00:18:07,839 --> 00:18:08,879
I strangled her.

281
00:18:09,079 --> 00:18:10,000
Where's her body?

282
00:18:10,079 --> 00:18:11,200
At Qidian Middle School.

283
00:18:11,440 --> 00:18:13,280
I'll ask you one last time.
Who killed her?

284
00:18:13,280 --> 00:18:15,040
I killed her. I strangled her.

285
00:18:15,760 --> 00:18:17,040
I hid her in the concrete.

286
00:18:18,760 --> 00:18:20,119
The biological information

287
00:18:20,599 --> 00:18:22,480
shows it's not Zhou Na's body.

288
00:18:30,399 --> 00:18:32,559
It is Zhou Na.

289
00:18:32,680 --> 00:18:34,839
I told you that I killed her.

290
00:18:34,960 --> 00:18:36,480
Why are you still investigating?

291
00:18:36,480 --> 00:18:37,760
You must stop investigating.

292
00:18:37,960 --> 00:18:40,000
I killed her. I strangled her.

293
00:18:40,119 --> 00:18:41,480
And I hid the body.

294
00:18:41,680 --> 00:18:43,200
Why are you still investigating?

295
00:18:43,200 --> 00:18:45,520
I'm begging you. Stop investigating.

296
00:18:50,440 --> 00:18:51,319
Stop investigating.

297
00:18:53,359 --> 00:18:54,040
I did it.

298
00:18:55,760 --> 00:18:56,559
I did it.

299
00:19:05,399 --> 00:19:06,599
Evidence shows

300
00:19:07,240 --> 00:19:08,520
that you are not the murderer.

301
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:11,480
We're placing you
under bail pending trial.

302
00:19:11,879 --> 00:19:14,040
But until everything is settled...

303
00:19:14,159 --> 00:19:15,288
You must stay in the city

304
00:19:15,920 --> 00:19:17,599
and remain available around the clock.

305
00:19:18,159 --> 00:19:20,040
Besides, you and Ren Xiaoming

306
00:19:20,079 --> 00:19:22,040
are both involved in the case.

307
00:19:22,399 --> 00:19:25,040
To avoid witness tampering
and collusion,

308
00:19:25,280 --> 00:19:26,119
let me remind you...

309
00:19:26,319 --> 00:19:27,960
You must not contact or meet each other.

310
00:19:28,280 --> 00:19:31,119
If you have no questions,
sign the bail agreement.

311
00:19:31,920 --> 00:19:32,720
Sign here.

312
00:19:52,056 --> 00:19:55,352
(La City Police Qidaohezi Branch)

313
00:19:59,720 --> 00:20:00,280
Go ahead.

314
00:20:02,040 --> 00:20:03,040
She's out.

315
00:20:03,079 --> 00:20:03,920
She's out.

316
00:20:04,119 --> 00:20:05,240
She's out. Hurry.

317
00:20:05,520 --> 00:20:06,680
Will you still be together?

318
00:20:07,240 --> 00:20:07,839
Say something.

319
00:20:07,839 --> 00:20:09,440
Is Ren Xiaoming the main suspect?

320
00:20:10,520 --> 00:20:11,879
Is Ren Xiaoming guilty or not?

321
00:20:12,184 --> 00:20:12,839
Answer us.

322
00:20:12,839 --> 00:20:13,359
Answer us.

323
00:20:13,359 --> 00:20:14,079
Please answer.

324
00:20:14,552 --> 00:20:15,159
Answer us.

325
00:20:15,159 --> 00:20:15,768
Back off.

326
00:20:16,520 --> 00:20:17,960
- Will you still be together?
- Are you guilty?

327
00:20:18,328 --> 00:20:18,960
Step aside.

328
00:20:18,960 --> 00:20:19,879
- Back off.
- Will you still be together?

329
00:20:19,960 --> 00:20:21,599
- Will you still be together?
- What's wrong with you?

330
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:23,399
- Answer us.
- Is the case closed?

331
00:20:27,599 --> 00:20:28,599
Is the case closed?

332
00:20:28,599 --> 00:20:29,720
Can you answer?

333
00:20:30,040 --> 00:20:31,200
Will you still be together?

334
00:20:35,879 --> 00:20:36,680
Any plans?

335
00:20:38,040 --> 00:20:38,960
I'll look for Xiaoyu.

336
00:20:39,680 --> 00:20:40,399
Don't bother.

337
00:20:40,760 --> 00:20:41,440
We'll help you.

338
00:20:41,879 --> 00:20:43,680
That's part of your job.

339
00:20:44,359 --> 00:20:47,159
But I'm looking for Xiaoyu
out of a mother's instinct.

340
00:20:47,720 --> 00:20:49,159
Who wouldn't look for their child?

341
00:20:49,599 --> 00:20:51,960
Even wolves travel
thousands of miles to find their young.

342
00:20:52,639 --> 00:20:54,200
Ge Wenjun is dangerous.

343
00:20:54,760 --> 00:20:56,440
She might have taken Zhou Na's gun.

344
00:20:56,960 --> 00:20:58,960
She might be holding on to that.

345
00:20:59,040 --> 00:20:59,720
You know?

346
00:21:01,599 --> 00:21:02,839
One more reason to find Xiaoyu.

347
00:21:26,399 --> 00:21:27,240
The child.

348
00:21:28,680 --> 00:21:31,399
I mean, the child.

349
00:21:33,920 --> 00:21:35,440
You're asking if this child is yours?

350
00:21:37,720 --> 00:21:39,079
I know that child is mine.

351
00:21:40,319 --> 00:21:41,520
I wish I'd known.

352
00:21:42,399 --> 00:21:43,920
I shouldn't have drunk that night

353
00:21:47,159 --> 00:21:48,440
or published that book.

354
00:22:00,480 --> 00:22:01,119
What's wrong?

355
00:22:02,040 --> 00:22:02,920
Don't do that.

356
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:04,319
You can't catch a cold now.

357
00:22:04,319 --> 00:22:05,159
I feel nauseous.

358
00:22:05,520 --> 00:22:06,968
But you need to close the window.

359
00:22:09,119 --> 00:22:11,480
Don't mess with me.
You can't catch a cold.

360
00:22:13,399 --> 00:22:14,200
I feel sick.

361
00:22:16,119 --> 00:22:18,040
Still, you shouldn't open the window.

362
00:22:24,639 --> 00:22:25,272
Here.

363
00:22:25,680 --> 00:22:27,480
Throw up in here if you want.

364
00:22:27,879 --> 00:22:29,592
Take it. I'm closing the window.

365
00:22:35,639 --> 00:22:36,240
Pull over.

366
00:22:37,839 --> 00:22:38,399
For what?

367
00:22:40,120 --> 00:22:40,680
To throw up.

368
00:22:59,192 --> 00:23:00,728
Go ahead.

369
00:23:03,079 --> 00:23:03,760
Thanks.

370
00:23:08,280 --> 00:23:09,119
Head back first.

371
00:23:09,440 --> 00:23:10,520
I want to go home later.

372
00:23:11,839 --> 00:23:12,359
Okay.

373
00:23:13,760 --> 00:23:16,240
Right now, you need to rest.

374
00:23:16,520 --> 00:23:17,559
Don't overthink things.

375
00:23:18,520 --> 00:23:20,119
Don't worry about the lawsuit.

376
00:23:20,480 --> 00:23:22,639
I hired the best lawyer Mr. Luo.

377
00:23:24,119 --> 00:23:24,680
Mr. Luo?

378
00:23:25,040 --> 00:23:25,839
Yeah, Mr. Luo.

379
00:23:26,319 --> 00:23:29,048
The renowned criminal defense lawyer.

380
00:23:30,280 --> 00:23:31,240
He must be expensive.

381
00:23:33,119 --> 00:23:33,960
Forget about money.

382
00:23:34,520 --> 00:23:37,359
I persuaded him for a long time
before he agreed to take the case.

383
00:23:38,440 --> 00:23:40,720
Come back to Qingzhou with me.

384
00:23:40,960 --> 00:23:43,599
Let's talk to Mr. Luo face-to-face.

385
00:23:43,720 --> 00:23:44,680
I won't be going back.

386
00:23:45,680 --> 00:23:48,839
Liu Xiaoran, I'm divorcing you.

387
00:23:49,960 --> 00:23:52,119
We've gone back and forth on this.

388
00:23:52,240 --> 00:23:53,040
Aren't you tired?

389
00:23:55,399 --> 00:23:56,040
The lid.

390
00:23:57,920 --> 00:23:58,520
Get going.

391
00:24:00,760 --> 00:24:01,528
I'll go with you.

392
00:24:01,639 --> 00:24:03,159
I can't let you wander around.

393
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:05,639
This is my turf. Don't worry.

394
00:24:06,760 --> 00:24:07,359
Xiaoming.

395
00:24:11,639 --> 00:24:12,960
None of the three is the killer.

396
00:24:13,879 --> 00:24:15,079
We're back to square one.

397
00:24:15,720 --> 00:24:17,280
(Diary, Ren Xiaoming's)
Pen and leaves.

398
00:24:17,336 --> 00:24:18,392
(and Bai Shu's Confession)

399
00:24:18,879 --> 00:24:20,480
The pen was filled with deer blood.

400
00:24:20,960 --> 00:24:22,159
Who did that?

401
00:24:23,680 --> 00:24:25,079
We can find the deer first.

402
00:24:25,319 --> 00:24:27,319
Let's split up and search Qidaohezi

403
00:24:27,559 --> 00:24:29,119
for deer now.

404
00:24:53,559 --> 00:24:54,639
Oh my.

405
00:24:56,920 --> 00:24:57,760
Let's go.

406
00:24:58,879 --> 00:24:59,879
(Oh my.)

407
00:25:39,359 --> 00:25:39,960
Young lady.

408
00:25:49,399 --> 00:25:50,280
Slow down, Ma'am.

409
00:25:51,200 --> 00:25:53,599
This is the only deer farm
within 100 kilometers.

410
00:25:54,319 --> 00:25:55,440
Bankrupt for a decade.

411
00:25:55,520 --> 00:25:56,240
No deer left.

412
00:26:00,359 --> 00:26:01,200
Stop.

413
00:26:01,399 --> 00:26:01,960
What's wrong?

414
00:26:02,079 --> 00:26:03,359
This is way too slow.

415
00:26:03,879 --> 00:26:05,480
What if there are snakes?

416
00:26:19,040 --> 00:26:21,000
I'm actually pretty quick on my feet.

417
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:21,839
Just hurry up.

418
00:26:27,639 --> 00:26:28,312
Be careful.

419
00:26:35,559 --> 00:26:36,280
Deer Farm.

420
00:26:36,760 --> 00:26:37,920
Ma'am, this is the place.

421
00:26:43,319 --> 00:26:44,440
This is a dryer.

422
00:27:00,240 --> 00:27:01,359
What is this? It stinks.

423
00:27:03,000 --> 00:27:03,736
Deer blood powder.

424
00:27:04,520 --> 00:27:05,520
That thing is real?

425
00:27:06,040 --> 00:27:07,240
It's crazy expensive.

426
00:27:07,799 --> 00:27:09,079
My aunt had heart problems.

427
00:27:09,440 --> 00:27:11,119
My uncle searched for it everywhere.

428
00:27:16,720 --> 00:27:18,520
A construction site is under the weeds.

429
00:27:28,000 --> 00:27:28,559
Where are you?

430
00:27:28,680 --> 00:27:30,240
Over here, Ma'am.

431
00:27:30,480 --> 00:27:31,192
Here.

432
00:27:32,399 --> 00:27:33,200
Oh my.

433
00:27:33,399 --> 00:27:34,079
Are you okay?

434
00:27:34,799 --> 00:27:36,760
I-I think I hit my tailbone, Ma'am.

435
00:27:37,440 --> 00:27:38,879
Did I break it?

436
00:27:38,960 --> 00:27:39,960
I can barely move.

437
00:27:40,200 --> 00:27:41,879
Turn your head and look at me.

438
00:27:42,359 --> 00:27:43,200
I can't.

439
00:27:43,280 --> 00:27:44,960
Try looking up at me.

440
00:27:47,119 --> 00:27:48,799
You're fine. You can turn your head.

441
00:27:48,960 --> 00:27:49,480
Wait.

442
00:27:49,480 --> 00:27:50,616
Hold on, Ma'am.

443
00:27:53,920 --> 00:27:54,520
Leaves.

444
00:27:59,639 --> 00:28:00,680
Not that one, Ma'am.

445
00:28:01,839 --> 00:28:03,680
Look up there.

446
00:28:05,599 --> 00:28:06,520
North American linden.

447
00:28:46,520 --> 00:28:50,104
(Bai Shu's childhood)

448
00:28:54,040 --> 00:28:55,520
You found me.

449
00:28:57,040 --> 00:28:58,440
You actually found me.

450
00:28:59,240 --> 00:29:00,319
You're amazing.

451
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:02,799
Kiss me.

452
00:29:44,568 --> 00:29:45,592
(Name: Bai Shu)

453
00:29:45,656 --> 00:29:46,808
(Blood Test Report)

454
00:29:46,872 --> 00:29:48,920
(Cardiomegaly observed.
Cardiac crux not clearly seen.)

455
00:29:49,016 --> 00:29:52,024
(Conclusion:
Congenital Ventricular Septal Defect)

456
00:29:53,752 --> 00:29:56,408
(Prescriptions
of Qidaohezi People's Hospital)

457
00:29:59,160 --> 00:30:00,312
(Medical Records,
congenital ventricular septal defect)

458
00:30:00,312 --> 00:30:01,336
(Mild tricuspid regurgitation)

459
00:30:02,359 --> 00:30:03,159
Bai Shu.

460
00:30:08,399 --> 00:30:10,079
Although I didn't give birth to you,

461
00:30:12,040 --> 00:30:13,960
I gave you a second life.

462
00:30:16,000 --> 00:30:17,879
That makes us connected by blood.

463
00:30:18,960 --> 00:30:19,920
But you show

464
00:30:22,760 --> 00:30:23,920
no sign of gratitude.

465
00:30:32,520 --> 00:30:34,280
You didn't give me a second life.

466
00:30:35,639 --> 00:30:37,200
You're turning me into a dead person.

467
00:30:39,280 --> 00:30:40,639
Look at your feet.

468
00:30:52,079 --> 00:30:54,040
What you're looking for
is in the cabinet.

469
00:31:26,000 --> 00:31:27,200
Those are deer blood powder.

470
00:31:27,288 --> 00:31:28,824
(Deer blood powder)

471
00:31:29,079 --> 00:31:30,399
Look at those bottles.

472
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:34,599
Look at the dates on them.

473
00:31:37,336 --> 00:31:38,424
(Deer blood powder,
produced on June 30, 1994)

474
00:31:40,696 --> 00:31:42,200
(Deer blood powder,
produced on May 6, 1995)

475
00:31:44,696 --> 00:31:46,552
(Deer blood powder,
produced on September 29, 1999)

476
00:31:53,144 --> 00:31:54,968
(Deer blood powder,
produced on December 8, 2010)

477
00:31:57,319 --> 00:31:59,240
Captain Li, the test results are in.

478
00:31:59,639 --> 00:32:00,760
The cement grade in this pit

479
00:32:01,000 --> 00:32:02,839
matches that of the statue base.

480
00:32:03,920 --> 00:32:04,568
Alright.

481
00:32:06,319 --> 00:32:07,799
North American linden leaves

482
00:32:08,399 --> 00:32:11,040
fell into this cement-pouring pit

483
00:32:11,399 --> 00:32:13,799
and were brought to
Qidian Middle School in the base.

484
00:32:14,720 --> 00:32:17,960
So this is the body disposal site.

485
00:32:18,480 --> 00:32:19,559
Yanzi, go check

486
00:32:19,760 --> 00:32:22,280
the information about personnel
of Deer Farm for 2010.

487
00:32:22,680 --> 00:32:25,799
Ma'am, I discovered it.

488
00:32:25,920 --> 00:32:27,599
Get him out of here.

489
00:32:27,720 --> 00:32:28,639
I contributed.

490
00:32:29,119 --> 00:32:29,760
Li.

491
00:32:32,079 --> 00:32:34,079
Deer blood is good for your heart.

492
00:32:35,119 --> 00:32:37,000
But I never let you have any.

493
00:32:39,319 --> 00:32:40,319
Guess why?

494
00:32:42,440 --> 00:32:45,079
Haven't you been
searching for your birth mother?

495
00:32:47,920 --> 00:32:50,639
The deer blood powder came from her.

496
00:33:00,559 --> 00:33:03,159
Captain Li, on the Deer Farm staff list,

497
00:33:03,159 --> 00:33:05,079
we found someone named Zhang Cuiping.

498
00:33:06,200 --> 00:33:06,960
It's strange.

499
00:33:07,159 --> 00:33:08,839
The year Bai Shu was adopted,

500
00:33:09,040 --> 00:33:10,599
she volunteered at that orphanage.

501
00:33:11,200 --> 00:33:14,480
When Bai Shu had heart surgery
at Qidaohezi People's Hospital,

502
00:33:15,000 --> 00:33:16,879
she worked as a cleaner there.

503
00:33:17,200 --> 00:33:19,319
When Bai Shu worked at Rest Cemetery,

504
00:33:19,520 --> 00:33:21,040
she worked at the deer farm

505
00:33:21,040 --> 00:33:22,159
- Zhang Cuiping.
- nearby.

506
00:33:22,760 --> 00:33:23,599
Such a coincidence?

507
00:33:28,319 --> 00:33:30,639
I know why you don't want us
to keep investigating.

508
00:33:31,639 --> 00:33:34,559
There was a worker at the deer farm
named Zhang Cuiping.

509
00:33:36,000 --> 00:33:37,720
In 1988, she gave birth to a daughter

510
00:33:38,040 --> 00:33:39,992
who was diagnosed
with congenital heart disease.

511
00:33:40,879 --> 00:33:42,599
Later, that girl went missing.

512
00:33:43,240 --> 00:33:44,480
Zhang Cuiping got divorced.

513
00:33:46,399 --> 00:33:47,480
Who is this child?

514
00:33:50,936 --> 00:33:51,896
(Silence)

515
00:33:51,896 --> 00:33:55,416
(Qidaohezi, 1993)

516
00:33:55,416 --> 00:33:56,440
(Ward 2)

517
00:34:04,520 --> 00:34:05,159
Sweetie.

518
00:34:18,559 --> 00:34:19,119
Ma'am.

519
00:34:20,480 --> 00:34:21,040
Get out.

520
00:34:25,759 --> 00:34:26,920
What do you want?

521
00:34:27,599 --> 00:34:28,184
I...

522
00:34:32,800 --> 00:34:34,400
I can give the child back to you.

523
00:34:36,079 --> 00:34:38,800
No, I don't have money for her surgery.

524
00:34:39,239 --> 00:34:41,360
Ma'am, please.

525
00:34:41,639 --> 00:34:42,719
You must cure her.

526
00:34:43,559 --> 00:34:45,119
I'll never come to see her again.

527
00:34:56,184 --> 00:35:00,408
(Qidaohezi, 1994)

528
00:35:24,760 --> 00:35:27,192
(Deer blood powder,
produced on July 3, 1994)

529
00:35:29,719 --> 00:35:30,639
You've seen her.

530
00:35:31,520 --> 00:35:33,599
She said she wouldn't see you again,

531
00:35:34,639 --> 00:35:37,079
but she stayed in Qidaohezi

532
00:35:39,040 --> 00:35:41,759
and kept visiting you sneakily.

533
00:35:42,200 --> 00:35:43,279
(Qidaohezi, 2004)

534
00:35:43,279 --> 00:35:44,759
(Remember that time)

535
00:35:44,840 --> 00:35:46,880
(I slapped you at the school gate?)

536
00:35:47,639 --> 00:35:49,639
(It was because she was spying again.)

537
00:35:50,599 --> 00:35:51,639
(All these years,)

538
00:35:51,759 --> 00:35:54,599
(I picked you up and dropped you off)

539
00:35:54,880 --> 00:35:56,440
(just to keep her away from you.)

540
00:35:57,079 --> 00:35:59,759
(That slap was for her to see.)

541
00:36:01,119 --> 00:36:04,199
If you make a mistake,
you face punishment.

542
00:36:05,239 --> 00:36:08,000
In 2010, Ge Wenjun

543
00:36:09,840 --> 00:36:12,880
came to me with a video
of Ren Xiaoming committing murder.

544
00:36:13,800 --> 00:36:16,248
She told me to hide

545
00:36:16,824 --> 00:36:17,784
Zhou Na's corpse.

546
00:36:18,599 --> 00:36:19,440
Others

547
00:36:20,840 --> 00:36:22,559
wouldn't be so manipulated like I was.

548
00:36:23,960 --> 00:36:25,639
It happened that I was in charge

549
00:36:26,040 --> 00:36:28,320
of the renovation
of Qidian Middle School.

550
00:36:30,000 --> 00:36:31,840
So, I chose to hide it

551
00:36:32,480 --> 00:36:34,800
in the statue base at the school gate.

552
00:36:35,320 --> 00:36:37,759
Back then, I truly believed

553
00:36:38,639 --> 00:36:40,400
that it was Zhou Na in there.

554
00:36:45,199 --> 00:36:47,520
Until a few days ago...

555
00:36:48,120 --> 00:36:49,119
(La City Police Qidaohezi Branch)

556
00:36:49,119 --> 00:36:50,440
(I was about to turn myself in.)

557
00:36:56,679 --> 00:36:59,880
You think those little tricks
you played with Bai Shu

558
00:37:00,559 --> 00:37:01,559
could fool me?

559
00:37:02,880 --> 00:37:03,960
Let me tell you.

560
00:37:05,159 --> 00:37:08,119
If you ever mess
with Bai Shu or Xiaoming again,

561
00:37:09,279 --> 00:37:11,400
I'll drag you down with me

562
00:37:13,320 --> 00:37:14,639
since I'm a dead man walking.

563
00:37:15,639 --> 00:37:16,559
Don't worry.

564
00:37:17,440 --> 00:37:20,679
I won't hand over that video.

565
00:37:23,040 --> 00:37:25,480
Get in the car. I need to talk to you.

566
00:37:26,960 --> 00:37:27,719
Not interested.

567
00:37:28,759 --> 00:37:30,440
I'm rushing to confess
and seek leniency.

568
00:37:36,639 --> 00:37:38,440
The person in the cement isn't Zhou Na.

569
00:37:47,639 --> 00:37:51,000
She's been right by my side
all these years.

570
00:37:51,759 --> 00:37:52,320
Right?

571
00:37:54,559 --> 00:37:55,840
Why didn't you tell me?

572
00:37:56,920 --> 00:37:58,199
What gives her the right?

573
00:37:59,920 --> 00:38:01,400
She abandoned you.

574
00:38:02,960 --> 00:38:04,679
I am your real mother.

575
00:38:08,199 --> 00:38:09,239
Where is she now?

576
00:38:12,000 --> 00:38:13,639
In the police morgue.

577
00:38:14,800 --> 00:38:15,800
What did you say?

578
00:38:18,159 --> 00:38:20,279
She's the body found in the concrete.

579
00:38:22,239 --> 00:38:23,400
Who killed Zhang Cuiping?

580
00:38:31,480 --> 00:38:32,440
You killed her?

581
00:38:51,360 --> 00:38:52,119
Why?

582
00:38:57,040 --> 00:38:58,800
Because she rushed to do something

583
00:38:58,800 --> 00:39:01,679
that only a mother
should do for her daughter.

584
00:39:02,360 --> 00:39:04,800
(Qidaohezi Rest Cemetery, 2010)

585
00:39:04,800 --> 00:39:06,199
(All these years,)

586
00:39:06,400 --> 00:39:09,199
(she's been hiding nearby,
secretly watching you,)

587
00:39:10,520 --> 00:39:11,960
(and even recorded videos.)

588
00:39:13,679 --> 00:39:16,520
(She already broke our agreement.)

589
00:39:18,960 --> 00:39:20,079
(That day,)

590
00:39:20,199 --> 00:39:23,079
(she filmed your confrontation
with Zhou Na by chance)

591
00:39:28,119 --> 00:39:32,440
(and the moment
Ren Xiaoming stabbed Zhou Na.)

592
00:39:43,559 --> 00:39:46,599
See, she didn't withdraw the phone

593
00:39:46,759 --> 00:39:48,279
out of fear.

594
00:39:48,480 --> 00:39:50,639
Zhang Cuiping was putting the phone away

595
00:39:51,679 --> 00:39:53,079
to rush in to help Bai Shu.

596
00:39:55,400 --> 00:39:58,159
So Zhang Fang wasn't there at all.

597
00:39:58,520 --> 00:39:59,960
Zhang Cuiping took the video.

598
00:40:08,920 --> 00:40:10,759
(According to Bai Shu's testimony,)

599
00:40:11,880 --> 00:40:13,840
(they ran after stabbing Zhou Na,)

600
00:40:15,159 --> 00:40:16,480
(and Zhou Na chased after them.)

601
00:40:17,320 --> 00:40:19,040
(So it wasn't a fatal injury.)

602
00:40:22,520 --> 00:40:25,079
(But when Bai Shu went back,
Zhou Na was dead,)

603
00:40:25,199 --> 00:40:26,279
(and the gun was gone.)

604
00:40:31,239 --> 00:40:34,079
(It's highly likely
that Zhang Cuiping killed Zhou Na)

605
00:40:34,199 --> 00:40:35,040
(and took the gun.)

606
00:40:43,480 --> 00:40:45,400
(She wanted to protect
her daughter Bai Shu.)

607
00:40:54,040 --> 00:40:55,480
(What you're saying is possible,)

608
00:40:56,400 --> 00:40:58,880
(but we can't
jump to conclusions without evidence.)

609
00:40:59,880 --> 00:41:01,639
(But now I finally understand)

610
00:41:01,639 --> 00:41:03,224
(why there are loopholes)

611
00:41:03,224 --> 00:41:05,000
(in Ren Xiaoming
and Bai Shu's statements.)

612
00:41:07,159 --> 00:41:09,279
(Neither of them knew)

613
00:41:09,520 --> 00:41:11,440
(about Zhang Cuiping's existence.)

614
00:41:18,920 --> 00:41:21,840
This woman abandoned you

615
00:41:22,719 --> 00:41:24,840
(Deer Farm, Qidaohezi, 2010)
(and has been secretly following me.)

616
00:41:26,719 --> 00:41:27,520
(She meant to)

617
00:41:28,520 --> 00:41:31,079
(take you away from me.)

618
00:41:32,920 --> 00:41:36,400
(This time,
she thought her chance had come.)

619
00:42:03,960 --> 00:42:07,000
(Zhang Cuiping, that foolish woman.)

620
00:42:07,360 --> 00:42:10,239
(She didn't dispose of that pen,
thinking that)

621
00:42:11,880 --> 00:42:13,360
(filling it with deer blood)

622
00:42:13,719 --> 00:42:15,440
(and washing off your fingerprints)

623
00:42:16,000 --> 00:42:18,239
(would cover all traces.)

624
00:42:19,480 --> 00:42:20,320
(What a fool.)

625
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:12,808
=Vanished Name=
